h1 "Mobile First"
hr
center
  p Fuck
  br
  p That
  br
  p Shit.
br
p.s_vs Mobile First has to be the worst paradigm ever. It's complicated and difficult to visualise elements popping in as screen size expands. It only makes sense you'd reduce, rather than introduce complexity with smaller screen sizes.
p.s_vs Instead, elk uses a unique system of removing elements as the screen size gets smaller, a sort of reverse Mobile Last.
p.s_vs For example, hiding an element when on a Laptop resolution will also mean the element is hidden on a Mobile resolution also.

p Consider,
.m_vs
  script(src="https://gist.github.com/twentytwoo/ad6737bafd0139a64a8be3222a260126.js")

p Which produces,

.row.preview
  .col-4.hol.m_hs
    p I'm getting outta here when you're on a Laptop or smaller
  .col-8
    p I'm here to stay, forever.

p The first element inside the row will disappear on a Laptop, but it also won't be present on a Mobile either.
.row
  .full
    p Similarly you can use 
    code .sod/l/m
    p  to show elements when the user is on a certain device.

p A caveat of this approach is that elements can not specifically be hidden or shown only on one resolution. Hide and Show can also not be used on the same element at the same time.

